We at Upyng respect your privacy and are committed to protecting it. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have regarding your data.
1. Introduction
We at Upyng respect your privacy and are committed to protecting it. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have regarding your data.
2. Information We Collect
Upyng does not collect personally identifiable information by default.
All processing (such as regex testing, grok parsing, JSON formatting, and text comparison) happens locally on your device.
If you choose to share logs or data via feedback forms, that information is stored only for the purpose of resolving issues.
3. Use of Information
Any information you voluntarily provide (e.g., through feedback or contact forms) is used solely to:
Improve our tools
Fix bugs
Respond to your inquiries
We do not sell, rent, or share your data with third parties.
4. Third-Party Services
Upyng does not directly use third-party analytics or advertising SDKs.
However, if you open external documentation links or use integrations, third-party sites may collect data according to their own privacy policies.
5. Data Security
We take appropriate measures to safeguard your information. However, please note that no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security of your data.
6. Cookies and Local Storage
The Upyng web app may use cookies or browser local storage for preferences (e.g., theme mode).
No personal or sensitive data is stored in cookies.
7. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect improvements or legal requirements. Any changes will be posted here with an updated effective date.
8. Contact Us
If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:
